Certainly! Here's an example of how you can automatically generate a table of contents (TOC) in a LaTeX document:

First, you will need to include the `tocloft` package in your LaTeX document's preamble, which is the section of the document that appears before the main content. You can do this by adding the following command to the preamble:
```
\usepackage{tocloft}
```
Next, you will need to specify the commands that you want to include in the TOC. For example, if you have sections named "Introduction", "Methods", "Results", and "Discussion", you can include them in the TOC like this:
```
\tableofcontents

% Define the sections to include in the TOC
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Introduction}
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Methods}
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Results}
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Discussion}
```
Finally, you can generate the TOC by including the following command in the document:
```
\printtoc
```
This will display the TOC at the top of the document, with the sections listed in the order they were specified.

Here's the complete example:
```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tocloft}

\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

% Define the sections to include in the TOC
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Introduction}
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Methods}
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Results}
\addcontentsline{toc}{part}{Discussion}

% Generate the TOC
\printtoc

% Main content goes here

\end{document}
```
This will generate a TOC with the sections listed in the order "Introduction", "Methods", "Results", and "Discussion".

Note that you can customize the appearance of the TOC by adjusting the formatting options provided by the `tocloft` package. For example, you can change the font size, color, and other attributes of the TOC entries by adding the following commands to the preamble:
```
\renewcommand\cfttoclineleaf{<your formatting here>}
\renewcommand\cfttocline{<your formatting here>}
```
You can also use other packages, such as `pdfpages` or `backmatter`, to automatically generate a table of contents for your document. These packages provide additional features and options for customizing the TOC, so you may want to consult their documentation for more information.

