```
This will produce a basic 8x8 chessboard with white and black squares, and the white and black pieces in the starting position.

You can customize the appearance of the chessboard by adjusting the `boardsize` option, changing the piece styles with the `setpiece` command, and specifying the initial position of the pieces using the `position` command.

For example, to create a larger board with a different piece style and starting position, you could use the following code:
```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chess}

\begin{document}

\begin{board}
  \boardsize{10x10}
  \setpiece{white}{white}
  \setpiece{black}{black}
  \position{start}
\end{board}

\end{document}
```
This will produce a 10x10 chessboard with the white and black pieces in the starting position.

You can also use the `fen` command to specify the FEN notation of the board. For example:
```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chess}

\begin{document}

\begin{board}
  \boardsize{8x8}
  \setpiece{white}{white}
  \setpiece{black}{black}
  \position{start}
  \fen{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR}
